# Tailwind CSS v4 Usage

## Configuration
- **CSS-First Config:** All theme customization in [globals.css](mdc:src/app/globals.css) using `@theme` directive
- **No JavaScript Config:** Avoid `tailwind.config.js` - use CSS variables instead
- **Theme Variables:** Use `--color-*` format for colors, `--font-*` for fonts

## Color System
- **OKLCH Format:** All colors defined in OKLCH for better color manipulation
- **CSS Variables:** Access theme colors via `var(--color-primary)` in custom CSS
- **Semantic Naming:** Use semantic color names (primary, secondary, accent, etc.)

## Font Integration
- **Next.js Fonts:** Use `@next/font/google` for font optimization
- **CSS Variables:** Define fonts in `@theme` block as `--font-sans`
- **Font Classes:** Apply via `font-sans`, `font-mono` utility classes

## Custom Utilities
- **Brand Classes:** Use custom utility classes like `.brand-primary`, `.premium-shadow`
- **Component Classes:** Define reusable component styles in `@layer utilities`
- **Accessibility:** Include focus states and reduced motion support

## Best Practices
- **No Arbitrary Values:** Use theme variables instead of arbitrary CSS values
- **Consistent Spacing:** Use standard Tailwind spacing scale
- **Dark Mode:** Ensure all custom colors have dark mode variants
- **Performance:** Leverage CSS variable inheritance for better performance
